(1+x)^p{}{}
f(x)=(1+x)^p
f'(x)=p(1+x)^{p-1}
...
f^{(n)}(x)= \frac{p!}{(p-n)!} (1+x)^{p-n}
...
x=0
f(0)=(1+0)^p=1
f'(0)=p(1+0)^{p-1}=p
...
f^{(n)}(0)= \frac{p!}{(p-n)!} (1+0)^{p-n}= \frac{p!}{(p-n)!} 
...
f(x)=f(0)+\frac{f'(0)}{1!}x+\frac{f''(0)}{2!}x^2+...+\frac{f^{(n)}(0)}{n!}x^n+...=
=1+px+\frac{p!}{2!(p-2)!}x^2+...+\frac{p!}{n!(p-n)!}x^n+...
